#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: effect-multiarg-op
---

# 2-arg effect op through an imported handler (busi Journal shape)

Regression for `match: no arm for append/2` (BUGS.md `v2-effect-multiarg-op`):
`Journal.append(scope, fact)` carries two payload args, and the handler arm
`case Journal.append(scope, fact, resume)` is append/3 — the v2 effect dispatch
packed the args into one Tuple2 payload (append/2) and no arm matched. Multi-arg
ops must reach the handler unpacked; the 1-arg op (`read`) stays a single payload.

[Journal, runJournal](./lib/effect-journal.ssc)

```scalascript
val log = runJournal(() => {
  Journal.append("acme", 100)
  Journal.append("acme", 50)
  Journal.append("other", 7)
  val xs = Journal.read("acme")
  xs.foldLeft(0)((a, b) => a + b)
})
println(log)
```
